Alexandra Posadzki reports: Canadian hacker Aubrey Cottle has pleaded guilty to three charges stemming from a cyberattack linked to notorious hacktivist group Anonymous on the Texas Republican Party. Mr. Cottle, who appeared in court in Newmarket, Ont., on Thursday, pleaded guilty to fraudulently obtaining a computer service, namely the systems of web-hosting company Epik, causing mischief...<img alt="" height="0" src="https://databreaches.net/wp-content/plugins/wp-piwik/proxy/matomo.php?idsite=11&amp;rec=1&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fdatabreaches.net%2F2026%2F06%2F18%2Fcanadian-hacker-pleads-guilty-to-charges-for-cyberattack-on-texas-republican-website%2F%3Fpk_campaign%3Dfeed%26pk_kwd%3Dcanadian-hacker-pleads-guilty-to-charges-for-cyberattack-on-texas-republican-website&amp;action_name=Canadian%20hacker%20pleads%20guilty%20to%20charges%20for%20cyberattack%20on%20Texas%20Republican%20website&amp;urlref=https%3A%2F%2Fdatabreaches.net%2Ffeed%2F" style="border: 0; width: 0; height: 0;" width="0" />
