On April 19, 2026, Cherry Health in Michigan detected suspicious network activity. Investigation revealed that an unknown person or persons had gained access to its network and copied data. On June 18, Cherry Health published a preliminary notice on its website.  The notice makes no mention of any earlier reporting on the incident that had...<img alt="" height="0" src="https://databreaches.net/wp-content/plugins/wp-piwik/proxy/matomo.php?idsite=11&amp;rec=1&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fdatabreaches.net%2F2026%2F06%2F22%2Fcherry-health-provides-preliminary-notice-of-recent-data-breach%2F%3Fpk_campaign%3Dfeed%26pk_kwd%3Dcherry-health-provides-preliminary-notice-of-recent-data-breach&amp;action_name=Cherry%20Health%20provides%20preliminary%20notice%20of%20recent%20data%20breach&amp;urlref=https%3A%2F%2Fdatabreaches.net%2Ffeed%2F" style="border: 0; width: 0; height: 0;" width="0" />
